        "body": "> but I have a feeling we may have better luck encouraging the use of map_partitions when the user/dev knows munual fusion makes the most sense .\r\n\r\nYeah, that's fair. I have a general desire to make pandas best-practices also work with dask dataframes, but it may be unrealistic to expect too much. That being said, I don't think computations like these (lots of embarrassingly parallel transformations) are particularly unusual in an ETL context, so it's a pathological case that I expect to see in the wild.",
